	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm only a lvl 20 druid myself but here is what I've learned.&nbsp;&nbsp;I mostly solo'ed my way up to 20 and when I did group I noticed that I had to be careful with my heals.  They can really annoy mobs and bring you unwanted attention.  This is especially true if your tank has 2 mobs on him.  Don't stand too close to the person you're healing as this increases the chance of aggro.<br><br>Before lvl 19/20 you should do some melee since your spells are really weak (heck, kiting isn't even possible until you get sow at lvl 14) and its nice to get your dodge skill up.  Afterwards, you shouldn't even think about melee as you don't have ac, hp or dmg to make it worthwhile.<br><br>Prior to kiting my tactic was snare, root and rot with melee to finish off the mob.  You need snare to give you time to run and recast root if it is resisted or it drops.  Once root holds, dot the mob and med until you get the root wears off message.  Rinse and repeat until mob is low on hp and melee to finish him off.  This will also give you a good idea of how much damage mobs can do to you.  EQAtlas.com has a good hunting guide, broken down by levels.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
